ical predictions for the stress-overshoot are shown to be in\ngood agreement with experimental observations in the metastable ultra-dense\nregime of hard-sphere colloidal suspensions as a function of shear-rate and\npacking fraction, and accounting for deformation-assisted activated motion is\ncrucial for both the transient and steady-state responses.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 17 Aug 2022 17:27:11 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-03-22"}
